The Role
Job Summary:

Newly formed Capability Centre for Adobe and Hybris Development is looking for enthusiastic and experienced software engineer in SAP Commerce (previously known as Hybris) solution. This is an exciting opportunity if you are keen on delivering cutting edge customer propositions on SAP Commerce platform. You will be part of a fully fledged development team delivering solutions via close engagement and collaboration with business stakeholders.

Responsibilities:
Deliver user stories through Test Driven Development lifecycle (incl. writing automated test cases);
Write well tested, documented and peer-reviewed Java code. Perform review of other team members’ code;
Work collaboratively with QAs, Product Owners, Business Analysts, Support Specialists and DevOps team members to deliver business requirements;
Deliver integration with internal and external applications via RESTful webservices and Spring Batch;
Customize and configure SAP Commerce solution (incl. data models, services, workflows, configuration files) to meet the desired business requirements;

Support and mentor more junior team members.
Requirements
Essential Requirements:

At least 6+ years of experience in Information Technology domain, with at least 3+ years of developer experience on SAP Commerce (aka Hybris);
Experience in delivering enterprise level solutions, at least 1 fully participated and successfully delivered project on SAP Commerce platform;
Strong expertise in JAVA/J2EE technologies, including Spring Core, Integration and Batch;
Strong SAP Commerce backoffice configuration and development skills;
Strong expertise in Source Code Management tools (specifically GIT). Experience in CI/CD tools, such as Maven, Gradle and Jenkins;
Experience in cloud technologies and building RESTful webservices;
Experience in Agile project methodology and delivery, delivery management tools like JIRA and VSTS;
Strong communication and team working skills;
Keen to learn, expand knowledge and skills, explore new technologies and solutions.
Preferred Skills and Experience
SAP Commerce Cloud Developer certification or equivalent.

Preferred Skills and Experience:

SAP Commerce Cloud Developer certification or equivalent
Company Description
Shell began operations in India more than 80 years ago. At Shell India, we invest in our people through our industry-leading development programmes, which see our employees, thrive and gain access to experts on a local and global level. To date, we have invested more than US$ 1 billion already in India’s energy sector alone, in socially and environmentally responsible ways. Shell is the only global major to have a fuel retail license in India.
Shell has established a new IT hub in Bangalore, and plans to scale it up over a five year period. The purpose of the IT Hub is to enable the Business by focusing on business outcomes, delivering fit for business technology solutions which enable business agility and profitable growth. .
